"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rzl1665702793282.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rzl1665702793282.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rzl1665702793282.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rzl1665702793282\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Structure Editor (Project)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Structure Editor of a project to create new main development objects, and add existing objects to a project so that the can be managed and built together.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rzl1665702793282__p_d5390e1_d5391e1_d5392e1\">The Structure Editor displays lists references to main development objects. A project can also contain other projects. You can add and open main development objects, and delete object references.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"rzl1665702793282__note_w3409ab1b5b3_w3410ab1b5_w3411ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Deleting an object reference does not delete the development object from the Repository.</div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rzl1665702793282__section_z1p_z12_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d258483e57\">How to</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"rzl1665702793282__ul_o3r_1b2_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rzl1665702793282__li_d2468e1_d2469e1_d2470e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"okr1665702619654.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/okr1665702619654.html\" title=\"New development objects may be created using templates and modeled objects. For main development objects, such as components and entities, it is also possible to create new object by duplicating an existing object.\">Create a New Development Object</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rzl1665702793282__li_d2471e1_d2472e1_d2473e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zum1665702619077.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zum1665702619077.html\" title=\"You can rename an object in-line in the Structure Editor, or in the Properties Inspector.\">Rename a Development Object</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rzl1665702793282__li_d2474e1_d2475e1_d2476e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xok1665702686298.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xok1665702686298.html\" title=\"Each main development object is opened in its own editor.\">Open a Main Development Object for Editing</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"rzl1665702793282__ul_r3r_1b2_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rzl1665702793282__li_d2477e1_d2478e1_d2479e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hkq1665702549855.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hkq1665702549855.html\" title=\"Use the Project Editor to create new Main Development Objects, add existing objects to the Project, and compile all objects referenced by the Project, and perform other project-level actions.\">Working with Projects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531861\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531861\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Structure Editor (Project) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Structure Editor (Project) Use the Structure Editor of a project to create new main development objects, and add existing objects to a project so that the can be managed and built together. The Structure Editor displays lists references to main development objects. A project can also contain other projects. You can add and open main development objects, and delete object references. Note: Deleting an object reference does not delete the development object from the Repository. How to Create a New Development Object Rename a Development Object Open a Main Development Object for Editing Working with Projects Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}